spans.text: The vestige of an ancient abbey
The vestige of an ancient abbey
by a ruined castle's rude remains
many a broken bust , And obelisk , and urn , overthrown by time
their banks and pebbly bottoms dry
Contemplation , to the crowd unknown , Her attitude composed , and aspect sweet !
the crushed wall a time-corroded cross , Religion like ,
that brown-browed isle ; Many rapt hours might Meditation pass , Slow moving betwixt the pillars of the pile
moving betwixt the pillars of the pile
Where now the sacred altar lies overturned
the fell tyrant of the tomb

The bones of an illustrious chieftain
The trophies of a broken fame
many a softening sound , Ravens and rooks , the birds of discord dwell
The lizard , and the lazy lurking bat
The lizard , and the lazy lurking bat
the sage matron and her maidens
the sage matron and her maidens
the limpid tide To pure canals , a crystal cool supply
Brightened his fleecy moments as they flew
wanton at the smiles of beauty more
the deep statesman , skilled in great design , Protract , but for a day , precarious breath ; Or the tuned follower of the sacred nine , Sooth , with his melody , insatiate Death
Strikes the devoted victim to the ground
Unerring , and unseen , the shaft of fate
— " This son of power , " This Saladin , to whom the nations bowed ; " May , in the space of one revolving hour , " Boast of no other spoil , but yonder shroud ! "
while Memory weeps the bloodstained field
